The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | BoI net zooms 91%
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      BoI net zooms 91%
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Mumbai, Oct. 22: State-owned Bank of India (BoI), which posted a 91 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 617 crore for the second quarter of the current fiscal, is bullish on maintaining high profit growth on the back of increasing credit demand. Net profit in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal was Rs 323 crore.        
	Higher interest income and low base effect along with lower provisioning for stressed loans on a sequential basis pushed up earnings, chairman and managing director Alok K. Misra told reporters here today.        
	The bank expects a 19 per cent rise in credit and a similar growth in deposits.        
	BoIs global business registered a 22 per cent growth at Rs 4,25,448 crore in the second quarter. Advances at Rs 1,84,377 crore rose 23 per cent, while deposits increased 21 per cent to Rs 2,41,071 crore. Net interest income rose 26 per cent to Rs 1,776 crore from Rs 1,409 crore a year ago.                                                                                                                                       
